item.description: The AMG-Mercedes C-Klasse DTM 1995 is one of the most iconic touring cars to ever compete in the European racing scene. The DTM became international in 1995 through the parallel inception of the International Touring Car Series (ITC) with races in Italy, Finland, the United Kingdom, Portugal and France. Mercedes driver Bernd Schneider dominated the season and clinched both titles.
